'''Tomás Lemos Araújo''' ({{IPA|pt|tuˈmaz ɐɾɐˈuʒu}}; born 16 May 2002) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Centre Back|centre-back]] or a [[Full-back (association football)|right-back]] for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

Coming through [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s youth system, Araújo impressed during his time with [[S.L. Benfica B|the reserve side]], winning the [[UEFA Youth League]] in [[2021–22 UEFA Youth League|2021–22]], being instrumental part of Benfica's first European trophy in 60 years. He was promoted to the first team in 2021, and subsequently loaned to [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] in 2022. He returned to Benfica in 2023, established himself as an integral player in the following years.

Araújo is a former [[Portugal national youth football team|Portugal youth international]], representing his country at various levels. He made his [[Portugal national football team|senior international debut]] in 2024.

==Club career==
===Benfica===
====2020–22: Early career====
Araújo joined [[Benfica Campus|Benfica's academy]] in 2016, aged 14, having previously played at youth level for Operário Famalicão, Palmeiras FC and Evolution Soccer Academy.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=24 July 2023 |title=Tomás Araújo: "O Benfica é a minha casa desde os 14 anos" |trans-title=Tomás Araújo: "Benfica is my house since 14 years old" |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/tomas-araujo-o-benfica-e-a-minha-casa-desde-os-14-anos |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=SAPO Desporto |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 22 May 2018, he signed his first professional contract with Benfica, until 2021.<ref>{{Cite web |date=22 May 2018 |title=Tomás Araújo assina contrato profissional |trans-title=Tomás Araújo signs professional contract |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-betclic/benfica/detalhe/tomas-araujo-assina-contrato-profissional |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Record |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

After rising through the club's youth ranks, Araújo made his professional debut for [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica's B team]] on 19 September 2020, coming off the bench to replace [[Pedro Ganchas]] on the 71st minute of a 6–0 victory away at [[Casa Pia A.C.|Casa Pia]], in the [[Liga Portugal 2]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 September 2020 |title=Benfica B avassalador com goleada e um hat-trick |trans-title=Benfica B overwhelming with thrashing and an hat-trick |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2020/09/19/direto-futebol-jogo-casa-pia-benfica-b-2-jornada-2-liga |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=SL Benfica |language=pt-PT}}</ref> He made his first professional start on 24 October, playing the full 90 minutes in a 1–0 league defeat at home against [[Académico de Viseu F.C.|Académico de Viseu]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 October 2020 |title=Benfica B-Ac. Viseu, 0-1: triunfo viseense na estreia do técnico Pedro Duarte |trans-title=Benfica B-Ac. Viseu, 0-1: "viseense" triumph in manager Pedro Duarte's debut |url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/benfica-b-academico-de-viseu-em-direto |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Record |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On 16 January 2021, Araújo scored his first professional goal, the opener in a 2–2 league draw at home to [[Académica de Coimbra (football)|Académica de Coimbra]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=16 January 2021 |title=Vitória escapa nos instantes finais |trans-title=Victory escapes in the final instants |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2021/01/16/futebol-direto-benfica-b-academica-16-jornada-ii-liga |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=SL Benfica |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 2 March, Araújo signed a new deal with Benfica. The duration of the contract was undisclosed.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 March 2021 |title=Tomás Araújo renova contrato |trans-title=Tomás Araújo renews contract |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2021/03/02/futebol-benfica-tomas-araujo-renovacao-contrato |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=SL Benfica |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 15 December 2021, aged 19, Araújo made his debut for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]'s main team, starting and playing the full match in a 3–0 home victory over [[S.C. Covilhã|Sporting da Covilhã]] in the [[Taça da Liga]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 December 2021 |title=Tomás Araújo: estreia pela equipa A aos 19 anos |trans-title=Tomás Araújo: debut for A team at 19 years old |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2021/12/15/futebol-declaracoes-tomas-araujo-pos-jogo-benfica-sc-covilha-3-jornada-grupo-a-taca-da-liga |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=SL Benfica |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On 27 February 2022, he made his [[Primeira Liga]] debut, coming off the bench to replace [[Jan Vertonghen]] in extra-time of a 3–0 home victory over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 February 2022 |title=A vitória mais expressiva da era Veríssimo, com ovação e braçadeira para Yaremchuck |trans-title=The most expressive victory of the Veríssimo era, with ovation and flag for Yaremchuk |url=https://www.dn.pt/desporto/a-vitoria-mais-expressiva-da-era-verissimo-com-ovacao-e-bracadeira-para-yaremchuck-14632184.html |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=Diário de Notícias |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On 13 May, Araújo made his first Primeira Liga start, playing the full match in a 2–0 victory away at [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Maia |first=Vítor |date=13 May 2022 |title=P. Ferreira-Benfica, 0-2 (crónica) |trans-title=P. Ferreira-Benfica, 0-2 (chronicle) |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga/pacos-ferreira/p-ferreira-benfica-0-2-cronica-165247650 |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

====2022–24: Loan to Gil Vicente and development====
On 27 July 2022, Benfica sent Araújo on a season-long [[Loan (sports)|loan]] to fellow Primeira Liga club [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 July 2022 |title=Oficial: Tomás Araújo emprestado pelo Benfica ao Gil Vicente |trans-title=Official: Tomás Araújo loaned by Benfica to Gil Vicente |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/oficial-tomas-araujo-emprestado-pelo-benfica-ao-gil-vicente-15052350.html |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=O Jogo |language=pt-PT}}</ref> He made his debut for the [[Barcelos, Portugal|Barcelos]] side on 18 August, starting in a 4–0 defeat away to [[AZ Alkmaar]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Europa Conference League qualifying phase and play-off round (Main Path)|play-off round]] of the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Cruz |first=André |date=18 August 2022 |title=Liga Conferência: AZ Alkmaar-Gil Vicente, 4-0 (crónica) |trans-title=Conference League: AZ Alkmaar-Gil Vicente, 4-0 (chronicle) |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/liga-conferencia/gil-vicente/liga-conferencia-az-alkmaar-gil-vicente-4-0-cronica |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 3 September, he made his first league appearance for Gil Vicente, coming on as a second-half substitute in a 2–0 home defeat to [[FC Porto|Porto]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |date=3 September 2022 |title=Gil Vicente perde com o FC Porto em Barcelos e já não ganha há quatro jogos |trans-title=Gil Vicente loses to FC Porto in Barcelos and hasn't won in four games |url=https://ominho.pt/gil-vicente-perde-com-o-fc-porto-em-barcelos-e-ja-nao-ganha-ha-quatro-jogos/ |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=O Minho |language=pt-PT}}</ref> Araújo scored his first Primeira Liga goal on 5 March 2023, Gil Vicente's second in a 2–0 victory at home against [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Dantas |first=Nuno |date=5 March 2023 |title=Gil Vicente-Marítimo, 2-0 (destaques) |trans-title=Gil Vicente-Marítimo, 2-0 (highlights) |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/gil-vicente/maritimo/gil-vicente-maritimo-2-0-destaques |access-date=24 September 2023 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt-pt}}</ref>

At the end of the [[2022–23 Gil Vicente F.C. season|2022–23 season]], Araújo returned to Benfica and, having impressed on loan, on 24 July 2023, he signed a new contract with the ''Eagles'' until 2028.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 July 2023 |title=Tomás Araújo renova até 2028 |trans-title=Tomás Araújo renews until 2028 |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2023/07/24/futebol-benfica-tomas-araujo-renova-contrato-ate-2028 |access-date=24 September 2023 |publisher=SL Benfica |language=pt-pt}}</ref> On 3 October, Araújo made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut for Benfica, in a [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League group stage|group stage]] match away at [[Inter Milan]], coming off the bench in the first-half to replace the injured [[Alexander Bah]], and playing the rest of the game as a makeshift [[Right back|right-back]]; Benfica lost 1–0.<ref>{{Cite web |date=3 October 2023 |title=Alexander Bah lesiona-se em Milão e promove estreia de Tomás Araújo na Champions |trans-title=Alexander Bah injured in Milan and promotes Tomás Araújo's Champions debut |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/alexander-bah-lesiona-se-em-milao-e-promove-estreia-de-tomas-araujo-na-champions-35394873 |access-date=3 October 2023 |website=OneFootball |language=pt-pt}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 14 April 2024, in a 3–0 home win over [[Moreirense F.C.|Moreirense]] in the [[Primeira Liga]]. During the match, he sprained his right ankle, forcing him to miss rest of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flashscore.pt/noticias/futebol-liga-europa-titular-frente-ao-moreirense-tomas-araujo-obrigado-a-parar-devido-a-lesao/tEZRCYDE/|title=Titular frente ao Moreirense, Tomás Araújo obrigado a parar devido a lesão|date=15 April 2024}}</ref>

====2024–25: First-team breakthrough====
In October 2024, following the arrival of new manager [[Bruno Lage]], Araújo earned a place in the starting XI over [[António Silva (footballer)|António Silva]], starting in a 4–0 win over [[Atlético Madrid]] on 2 October in the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]]. Due to his passing quality when building from the back and speed, Lage considered him crucial for the team's dynamics, as he aided in covering defensive gaps and recovering quickly, making him a better fit for Lage's system. After capitalizing on his opportunities, with strong performances, he kept his place as a starter, due to also his reliability to play across different positions in the defense.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 October 2024 |title=Bruno Lage preferiu Tomás Araújo em vez de António Silva. Eis os motivos |trans-title=Bruno Lage preferred Tomás Araújo over António Silva. Here are the reasons. |url=https://www.cmjornal.pt/desporto/futebol/detalhe/bruno-lage-preferiu-tomas-araujo-em-vez-de-antonio-silva-explicamos-os-motivos |access-date=20 November 2024 |website=[[Correio da Manhã (Portugal)|Correio da Manhã]] |language=pt-pt}}</ref> He was named the league's Defender of the Month for November, after helping Benfica in the four-match winning streak, which included two clean sheets.<ref name=POTM>{{cite news|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/en/epocas/20242025/noticias/geral/premios/liga-portugal-betclic/novembro/tomas-araujo-distinguido-com-premio-sabseg-defesa-do-mes-da-liga-portugal-betclic/|title=Tomás Araújo wins SABSEG Defender of the Month in Liga Portugal Betclic|work=[[Primeira Liga|Liga Portugal]]|language=en|date=9 December 2024|access-date=16 December 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
With the [[Portugal national under-17 football team|Portugal under-17s]], Araújo took participated in the [[2019 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] in Ireland, playing four matches losing in the quarter-finals to [[Italy national under-17 football team|Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under17/match/2027445--italy-vs-portugal/|title=Portugal vs. Italy|website=[[UEFA]]|access-date=1 April 2025}}</ref>

On 24 March 2023, he earned his first [[Cap (sport)|appearance]] for the [[Portugal national under-21 football team|under-21 team]], starting in a 2–0 [[Exhibition game|friendly]] victory against [[Romania national under-21 football team|Romania]]. In June, he took part in the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036139--portugal-vs-belgium/|title=History: Portugal 2-1 Belgium &#124; UEFA Under-21 2023|website=UEFA|date=27 June 2023|access-date=18 June 2024|archive-date=14 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114105538/https://www.uefa.com/under21/match/2036139--portugal-vs-belgium/|url-status=live}}</ref> Portugal were eliminated from the tournament, on 2 July, after a 1–0 loss to [[England national under-21 football team|England]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66069220|first=Alex|last=Howell|title=England U21 1-0 Portugal U21|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=2 July 2023|access-date=14 July 2023|archive-date=11 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230711202505/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66069220|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 8 October 2024, Araújo received his first call-up to the [[Portugal national football team|senior squad]] for the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League|UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], as a replacement for the injured [[Gonçalo Inácio]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2024/10/08/futebol-benfica-tomas-araujo-convocado-selecao-nacional-liga-das-nacoes|title=Tomás Araújo chamado à Seleção Nacional|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|date=8 October 2024|language=pt}}</ref> On 18 November, he made his debut in a 1–1 draw against the latter; Portugal had already secured first place in their group with one fixture remaining.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Inês Braga|last=Sampaio|title=Tomás Araújo e Tiago Djaló "muito felizes" com a estreia na seleção|url=https://rr.pt/bola-branca/noticia/clube-portugal/2024/11/18/tomas-araujo-e-tiago-djalo-muito-felizes-com-a-estreia-na-selecao/402049/|website=Renasença|date=18 November 2024|access-date=1 April 2025|language=pt}}</ref>

